articles.title: South Africa's ruling ANC set to lose majority in pivotal vote, early results show - CNBC
articles.description: Early indications from 17.54% of polls show the ANC gaining 42.95% of support, with the Democratic Alliance (DA) wresting 25.24% of votes.
articles.content:
South African's governing African National Congress appears set to lose majority control in the country's most seismic political transition since the end of the apartheid.
